title: China’s CAS Space outlines rocket series, inaugurates manufacturing facility
summary: A Chinese space launch company has outlined its plans for a series of solid and reusable rockets for launch services and space tourism and opened a new industrial base.

title: Capella Space establishes new business unit focused on U.S. defense market
summary: Capella Space announced Jan. 31 it is forming a new business unit, Capella Federal, that will offer “increased Earth observation access to select U.S. defense customers.”

title: Xplore announces first launch of remote-sensing smallsat
summary: Xplore, a startup based in Redmond, Washington, announced Jan. 31 it was granted a remote-sensing license for the company's first mission to low Earth orbit.

title: LA-based Embedded Ventures launches inaugural fund, with focus on national security and space tech
summary: Los Angeles-based Embedded Ventures kicked off an inaugural $100 million fund, the firm announced Tuesday, as it looks to back companies building for both commercial and national security customers, especially in the space sector.

title: NASA hits limits of space station utilization
summary: NASA has effectively reached full utilization of the International Space Station given limitations on crew time and the ability to get cargo to and from the station, an agency official said Jan. 30.
